<page api="portableSql">
    <shortlink>portablesql character function</shortlink>
    <topic  parent="" parentType="" elementName="Character Portable SQL Function">Character</topic>
    <description>
        <p>Converts a numeric expression into a character expression.</p>
    </description>
    <prototypes>
        <prototype>Character as C (AsciiValue as N)</prototype>
    </prototypes>
    <arguments>
        <argument>
            <name>AsciiValue</name>
            <type>N</type>
            <description>
                <p>An ASCII value.</p>
            </description>
        </argument>
    </arguments>
    <returns>
        <return>
            <name>result</name>
            <type>C</type>
            <description>
                <p>Returns a character.</p>
            </description>
        </return>
    </returns>
    <discussion>
        <p>The Character function converts an ASCII value to a character.</p>
    </discussion>
    <example code="sql"  caption="Character() function executed on the Northwind Access database"><![CDATA[SELECT FIRST 1 Character(100) AS Expr1 FROM Customers
=d]]></example>
</page>